auto px-6\"><div class=\"text-center mb-12\"><h2 class=\"text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4\">Understanding THCa</h2><p class=\"text-slate-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto\">Learn about the compound, its legal complexities, and why regulations vary by state.</p></div><div class=\"grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6\"><div class=\"bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-2xl p-6 hover:border-slate-700 transition-colors\" style=\"opacity:0;transform:translateY(20px)\"><div class=\"text-3xl mb-4\">🧬</div><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3\">What is THCa?</h3><p class=\"text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed\">THCa (tetrahydrocannabinolic acid) is a non-psychoactive cannabinoid found in raw cannabis plants. It&#x27;s the precursor to THC and doesn&#x27;t produce intoxicating effects in its raw form.</p></div><div class=\"bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-2xl p-6 hover:border-slate-700 transition-colors\" style=\"opacity:0;transform:translateY(20px)\"><div class=\"text-3xl mb-4\">🔥</div><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3\">How Does Heating Affect THCa?</h3><p class=\"text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed\">When THCa is heated (decarboxylated) through smoking, vaping, or cooking, it converts to psychoactive THC. This is why the legal status can differ based on intended use.</p></div><div class=\"bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-2xl p-6 hover:border-slate-700 transition-colors\" style=\"opacity:0;transform:translateY(20px)\"><div class=\"text-3xl mb-4\">⚖️</div><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3\">Federal vs. State Law</h3><p class=\"text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed\">Under the 2018 Farm Bill, hemp products containing less than 0.3% Delta-9 THC are federally legal. However, states have their own regulations that may be more restrictive.</p></div><div class=\"bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-2xl p-6 hover:border-slate-700 transition-colors\" style=\"opacity:0;transform:translateY(20px)\"><div class=\"text-3xl mb-4\">